              <h3 id="group-drain-cleaning"><a href="../commercial-service/drain-cleaning/">Drain Cleaning</a></h3>
              <article class="service-line"><span>01</span><div><h4><a href="../commercial-service/drain-cleaning/floor-drain-cleaning/">Floor Drain Cleaning</a></h4><p>Commercial floor drains take everything: grease, food waste, mop water, and detergent. Cleaning them on a cadence prevents the slow drain that closes the kitche</p></div></article>
              <article class="service-line"><span>02</span><div><h4><a href="../commercial-service/drain-cleaning/storm-drain-cleaning/">Storm Drain Cleaning</a></h4><p>Storm drains overflow when they are full of leaves, sand, and trash. Cleaning before the rainy season is cheaper than parking-lot flooding.</p></div></article>
              <article class="service-line"><span>03</span><div><h4><a href="../commercial-service/drain-cleaning/catch-basin-cleaning/">Catch Basin Cleaning</a></h4><p>Catch basins capture grit and debris before it enters the storm system. They have to be vacuumed periodically or they stop catching anything at all.</p></div></article>
            </section>
            <section class="service-group" aria-labelledby="group-drain-support">
              <h3 id="group-drain-support">Drain support</h3>
              <article class="service-line"><span>04</span><div><h4><a href="../commercial-service/hydro-jetting/">Hydro Jetting</a></h4><p>Cabling cuts a hole through a clog. Jetting cleans the pipe wall so the line works at capacity, not at minimum flow.</p></div></article>
              <article class="service-line"><span>05</span><div><h4><a href="../commercial-service/drain-and-sewer-inspection/">Drain and Sewer Inspection</a></h4><p>Property managers and operators need real records, not opinions. Camera inspection with locating produces evidence that supports capital plans and repair decisi</p></div></article>
              <article class="service-line"><span>06</span><div><h4><a href="../commercial-service/drain-repairs/">Drain Repairs</a></h4><p>Repeat backups usually point to a defect in the pipe. Honest Drain finds the section that is failing, prices the fix clearly, and protects the operator's space </p></div></article>
            </section>
            <section class="service-group" aria-labelledby="group-sewer-maintenance">
              <h3 id="group-sewer-maintenance">Sewer and maintenance</h3>
              <article class="service-line"><span>07</span><div><h4><a href="../commercial-service/sewer-repair-and-replacement/">Sewer Repair and Replacement</a></h4><p>When the sewer fails, the operation is at risk. Spot repair, full replacement, and staged work plans each fit a different commercial situation.</p></div></article>
              <article class="service-line"><span>08</span><div><h4><a href="../commercial-service/sewer-cleaning/">Sewer Cleaning</a></h4><p>Commercial sewers move bigger volumes than residential ones and fail in larger ways. Scheduled cleaning keeps a single backup from closing the property.</p></div></article>
              <article class="service-line"><span>09</span><div><h4><a href="../commercial-service/maintenance-programs/">Maintenance Programs</a></h4><p>Backups are predictable when the building's drain system is understood. A documented maintenance program prevents the surprise call.</p></div></article>
            </section>
